BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
To remove the [`\frac{3}{7}`] from the left side, we need to _add_ [`\frac{3}{7}`] to each side of the equation.

[```\newcommand{\highlight}[1]{\mathchoice{\colorbox{lightsapphire}{$\displaystyle #1$}}{\colorbox{lightsapphire}{$\textstyle #1$}}{\colorbox{lightsapphire}{$\scriptstyle #1$}}{\colorbox{lightsapphire}{$\scriptscriptstyle #1$}}}\newcommand{\addright}[1]{{\highlight{{{}+#1}}}}\newcommand{\amp}{&}
\begin{aligned}
q-\frac{3}{7}\amp=\frac{3}{2}\\
q-\frac{3}{7}\addright{\frac{3}{7}}\amp=\frac{3}{2}\addright{\frac{3}{7}}\\
q\amp=\highlight{\frac{21}{14}}+\highlight{\frac{6}{14}}\\
q\amp=\frac{27}{14}
\end{aligned}
```]

We should check the solution by substituting [`\frac{27}{14}`] in for [`q`] in the original equation:

[```\newcommand{\substitute}[1]{{\color{blue}{{#1}}}}\newcommand{\confirm}[1]{\stackrel{\checkmark}{#1}}\newcommand{\wonder}[1]{\stackrel{\text{?}}{#1}}\newcommand{\amp}{&}
\begin{aligned}
q-\frac{3}{7}\amp=\frac{3}{2}\\
\substitute{\frac{27}{14}}-\frac{3}{7}\amp\wonder{=}\frac{3}{2}\\
\frac{27}{14}-\frac{6}{14}\amp\wonder{=}\frac{3}{2}\\
\frac{21}{14}\amp\wonder{=}\frac{3}{2}\\
\frac{3}{2}\amp\confirm{=}\frac{3}{2}
\end{aligned}
```]

The solution [`\frac{27}{14}`] is checked, and the solution set is [`\left\{\frac{27}{14}\right\}\text{.}`]

